Thank you for your interest in serving in the Care Ministry at FG! We have some great opportunities for you, such as Taste of Grace Ministry, our Physical Care Team, shut-in visitation, transportation, and financial coaches. You can serve on these as little or as often as you are available.  Finally, we need weekly leaders to help facilitate different Care Ministry Classes (Grief Share, Divorce Care and Divorce Care for Kids, Managing Your Finances Class, and Re|engage).  Please respond to find out more information!
Thank you for your interest in serving!

{{ 'Global' | Attribute:'EmailHeader' }} {% assign requester = Workflow | Attribute:'Requestor','Object' %} Dear {{ requester.NickName }},

Hello, my name is Kate Zerndt. I am the Care Ministry Assistant at Fellowship Greenville. I received your Serving Team Discovery form and wanted to give you more information on our Care Ministry volunteer opportunities. If any of these seem like an area you would like to serve in, please reply to this email.

One of our areas is the Taste of Grace Ministry. With Taste of Grace, we have two areas: Funeral and Recovery. We have about 60 volunteers on each list, so the requests are rotated through the volunteer list pretty well. If you are on the Funeral list and we are hosting a Funeral meal, volunteers will be asked to prepare one side dish (fruit salad, potato salad, dessert etc.) and drop it off at the church.

Then the Recovery side volunteers prepare and deliver a meal to someone's house after they are home from the hospital. This would be more of a casserole or full meal with some more personal contact if you were seeking this. It does not have to be homemade. Purchasing something is great too! You do NOT have to respond to every need. If you are available to serve when I email the group, you just let me know.

Our second largest group is our Physical Care Team. This team is a group of men who volunteer when able to help a Single mom or widow with home repairs, lawn maintenance and things of that nature. Usually, for these needs, I just send a bulk email to the group and they can respond IF they are available and skilled in that request etc.

We have other areas of serving in care, such as visitation to shut-ins, transportation to doctor’s appointments or church to those unable to drive, and financial coaches. You can serve on these as little or as often as you are available.

Finally, we need weekly Leaders to help facilitate different Care Ministry Classes. One Sundays morning we have 13-week sessions in Grief Share, Divorce Care and Divorce Care for Kids. We also offer a Managing Your Finances Class on Sunday mornings, which is a 7-week course. On Wednesday evenings we have a Marriage Enrichment class called Re|engage that we need leader couples to facilitate Closed Groups. We are always looking for additional leaders to help rotate with our current leaders.

Please let me know if any of these sound interesting to you and I will add you to these email lists. If you are added to any of these lists, it simply means that you, along with the entire group, will be emailed or called to see if you are available for a specific need. You can help out for that need or serve on another one at a future time. Feel free to call me if you have any questions.

Thank you so much for your heart to serve.

Kate Zerndt
Care Ministry Assistant
